x4freetext: Pulsed electrons on tantalum with Be-canned
boron-10 filter. Copper and lead shadow bars used to
reduce gamma flash and fast neutron flux from source.
Data from several samples were combined to derive
isotopic cross sections for pure isotopes. Slight
revision of neutron flux shape above 70-keV (less
than 6%) made referenced to U-235 fission cross
Prompt gammas from capture detected with pair
of C(6)F(6) liquid scintillators, 10-cm diameter by 4-
cm thick. Beam monitor is Li-6 glass scintillator,
strength functions are missing, it ignores
Sum of Breit-Wigner single level forms with
least squares fitting that included Doppler
and gamma widths could be fitted.
Statistical deviations for well defined peaks range
from 0.08 eV(at 2.7 keV) to 0.4 eV(at 11.4 keV).
